<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-08-29T00:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-08-29T00:35:00-05:00" n="594" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">701.9111/653: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Moose</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-29T09:00:00+03:25">August 29, 1938—9
                                        a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 9:20 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>95. Legation’s telegram 52 [<hi rend="italic">53</hi>], May 25, 11
                                a.m. I have just learned from a source believed to be trustworthy
                                that while Soheily was Minister of Foreign Affairs he suggested to
                                the Shah the reopening of the Iranian Legation in Washington and
                                that the Shah rejected the suggestion saying that the Americans had
                                been rude to Iran.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Moose</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>